net.kreatious.pianoleopard.history

Class HistoryVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.kreatious.pianoleopard.history.HistoryVisitor

  • public abstract class HistoryVisitor
extends Object
    Visits the events performed historically by the user.

    Methods are called from various threads, but are guaranteed to not be called concurrently.

    Author:
    Jay-R Studer

      • onFile

        public void onFile(byte[] hash,
                   long time)
        Called when the user has opened a file.
        Parameters:
        hash - the SHA-256 hash code of the file that was opened
        time - the epoch time in milliseconds the event was played at

      • onKey

        public void onKey(byte status,
                  byte data1,
                  byte data2,
                  long currentTime,
                  long time)
           throws InvalidMidiDataException
        Called when the user has pressed a key in the past.
        Parameters:
        status - the status byte of the message the user played
        data1 - the first data byte of the message
        data2 - the second data byte of the message
        currentTime - the current song time in microseconds the message was played at
        time - the epoch time in milliseconds the event was played at
        Throws:
        InvalidMidiDataException - if the message was invalid

      • onParsingComplete

        public abstract void onParsingComplete()
        Called after parsing is complete.

        This method may be called multiple times, and is guaranteed to be called at least once if the log file is accessible. If notifications are no longer desired, then the visitor needs to be unregistered.

        If the History class was unable to initialize logging, this method is never called.
